<paragraph blockId="48.[151,905,151,178]" box="[151,905,151,178]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,905,151,178]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" reason="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,905,151,178]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicName authority="Hewitson, 1868" authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1868" box="[151,591,151,178]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pteroteinon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laufella">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,393,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Pteroteinon laufella</emphasis>
Hewitson, 1868
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation author="Hewitson, W. C." box="[639,822,152,178]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refId="ref35304" refString="Hewitson, W. C. (1867 - 1871) Illustrations of new species of exotic butterflies. Vol. IV. John van Voorst, London, iii + 118 pp." type="book" year="1867">Hewitson 1867</bibRefCitation>
–1871)
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1438,222,1755]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<bibRefCitation author="Hewitson, W. C." box="[151,330,222,247]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refId="ref35304" refString="Hewitson, W. C. (1867 - 1871) Illustrations of new species of exotic butterflies. Vol. IV. John van Voorst, London, iii + 118 pp." type="book" year="1867">Hewitson (1867</bibRefCitation>
–1871) described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1868" box="[531,726,222,247]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laufella">
<emphasis box="[531,726,222,247]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Hesperia laufella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Akwa Akpa (=Old Calabar, south-eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1265,1354,222,247]" name="Nigeria" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
), and it is known from 
<collectingCountry box="[330,480,261,286]" name="Sierra Leone" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Sierra Leone</collectingCountry>
, east to 
<collectingCountry box="[579,699,261,286]" name="Cameroon" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
, and south to northern 
<collectingCountry box="[971,1054,261,286]" name="Angola" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Angola</collectingCountry>
and adjacent 
<collectingCountry box="[1217,1341,261,286]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">DR Congo</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Larsen, T. B." pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refId="ref35885" refString="Larsen, T. B. (2005) Butterflies of West Africa. 2 Vols. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, Denmark, 595 + 270 pp." type="book" year="2005">Larsen 2005</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Larsen, T. B." box="[232,393,300,325]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refId="ref35885" refString="Larsen, T. B. (2005) Butterflies of West Africa. 2 Vols. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, Denmark, 595 + 270 pp." type="book" year="2005">Larsen (2005)</bibRefCitation>
had no records from 
<collectingCountry box="[644,714,300,325]" name="Benin" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Benin</collectingCountry>
, but many have since been collected there by A. Coache (T.B. Larsen pers. comm. 2013) and MJWC has a male from Cotonou (
<date box="[893,1049,338,363]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1989-05-29">29 May 1989</date>
). There is a limited literature on it as a pest of oil palm in West Africa.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1438,222,1755]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,346,415,440]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Food plants.</emphasis>
As early as 1919 and 1929, this species was already appearing in German texts as a pest of oil palm in 
<collectingCountry box="[241,358,454,479]" name="Cameroon" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lepesme, P." box="[372,541,454,479]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refId="ref36020" refString="Lepesme, P. (1947) Les Insectes des Palmiers. Paul Lechevalier, Paris, 909 pp." type="book" year="1947">Lepesme 1947</bibRefCitation>
). As discussed in 
<bibRefCitation author="Cock, M. J. W." box="[740,892,454,479]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 63" refId="ref34130" refString="Cock, M. J. W. (2010 a) Observations on the biology of Afrotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera) principally from Kenya. Part 1. Introduction and Coeliadinae. Zootaxa, 2547, 1 - 63." type="journal article" year="2010">Cock (2010a)</bibRefCitation>
early reports of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Drury)" baseAuthorityName="Drury" box="[1075,1389,454,479]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pyrrhochalcia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iphis">
<emphasis box="[1075,1297,454,479]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Pyrrhochalcia iphis</emphasis>
(Drury)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" box="[151,467,493,518]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Coeliades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bixae">
<emphasis box="[151,335,493,518]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Coeliades bixae</emphasis>
(Linnaeus)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[484,622,493,518]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hesperiidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cock" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[638,774,493,518]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Coeliadinae">Coeliadinae</taxonomicName>
) feeding on palms are likely to be misidentifications for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1868" box="[151,374,532,557]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pteroteinon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laufella">
<emphasis box="[151,374,532,557]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Pteroteinon laufella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1438,222,1755]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
Thereafter, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1868" box="[332,560,570,595]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pteroteinon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laufella">
<emphasis box="[332,560,570,595]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Pteroteinon laufella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reappears in the economic literature for French West Africa. As discussed above under 
<taxonomicName authority=", Mariau &amp; Morin (1974)" authorityName=", Mariau &amp; Morin" authorityYear="1974" box="[301,837,609,634]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zophopetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerymica">
<emphasis box="[301,543,609,634]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Zophopetes cerymica</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D. &amp; Morin, J. P." box="[560,837,609,634]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="187 - 188" refId="ref36384" refString="Mariau, D. &amp; Morin, J. P. (1974) Les ravageurs et maladies du palmier a huile et du cocotier. Chenilles defoliatrices de la famille des Hesperidae en Afrique Occidentale. Oleagineux, 29 (4), 187 - 188." type="journal article" year="1974">Mariau &amp; Morin (1974)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
report on two hesperiid defoliators of oil palm and coconut: 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Mariau &amp; Morin" authorityYear="1974" box="[254,492,647,672]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zophopetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerymica">
<emphasis box="[254,492,647,672]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Zophopetes cerymica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName box="[538,695,647,672]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zophopetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dysmephila">
<emphasis box="[538,695,647,672]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Z. dysmephila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1868" box="[758,870,647,672]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pteroteinon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laufella">
<emphasis box="[758,870,647,672]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">P. laufella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but do not separate the two in their account of the damage, economic thresholds, and natural enemies. 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D. &amp; Desmier de Chenon, R. &amp; Julia, J. F. &amp; Philippe, R." box="[761,998,686,711]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="169 - 228" refId="ref36432" refString="Mariau, D., Desmier de Chenon, R., Julia, J. F. &amp; Philippe, R. (1981) Les ravageurs du palmier a huile et du cocotier en Afrique Occidentale. Oil palm and coconut pests in West Africa. Oleagineux, 36, 169 - 228." type="journal article" year="1981">
Mariau 
<emphasis box="[853,905,686,711]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">et al</emphasis>
. (1981)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D." box="[1062,1222,686,711]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refId="ref36315" refString="Mariau, D. (2000) Les ravageurs du palmier a huile et du cocotier: biologie, description et methodes de lutte. CIRAD, Montpellier, France, 1 disque optique numerique, CD-ROM." type="book" year="2000">Mariau (2000</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D." box="[1238,1295,686,711]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refId="ref36353" refString="Mariau, D. (2001) The fauna of oil palm and coconut: insect and mites pests and their natural enemies. CIRAD, Montpellier, 264 pp." type="book" year="2001">2001</bibRefCitation>
) summarise information on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1868" box="[327,441,725,750]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pteroteinon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laufella">
<emphasis box="[327,441,725,750]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">P. laufella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a pest of oil palm and coconut. In 
<collectingCountry box="[870,1024,725,750]" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Côte d’Ivoire</collectingCountry>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vuattoux, R." box="[1036,1221,725,750]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="562 - 568" refId="ref37364" refString="Vuattoux, R. (1999) Les lepidopteres hesperiides de la Station de Lamto (Cote d'Ivoire). Lambillionea, 94, 562 - 568." type="journal article" year="1999">Vuattoux (1999)</bibRefCitation>
reared this species primarily from oil palm (
<emphasis box="[448,1046,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Presque tous les adultes obtenus ont été élevés sur</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[1056,1259,764,789]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Elaeis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="guineensis">Elaeis guineensis</taxonomicName>
), and only 
<specimenCount pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
from coconut; these two food plants are repeated in Vande weghe (2010).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1438,222,1755]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,343,841,866]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Life history.</emphasis>
The published life history information (
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D. &amp; Morin, J. P." box="[798,1056,841,866]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="187 - 188" refId="ref36384" refString="Mariau, D. &amp; Morin, J. P. (1974) Les ravageurs et maladies du palmier a huile et du cocotier. Chenilles defoliatrices de la famille des Hesperidae en Afrique Occidentale. Oleagineux, 29 (4), 187 - 188." type="journal article" year="1974">Mariau &amp; Morin 1974</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D. &amp; Desmier de Chenon, R. &amp; Julia, J. F. &amp; Philippe, R." box="[1068,1280,841,866]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="169 - 228" refId="ref36432" refString="Mariau, D., Desmier de Chenon, R., Julia, J. F. &amp; Philippe, R. (1981) Les ravageurs du palmier a huile et du cocotier en Afrique Occidentale. Oil palm and coconut pests in West Africa. Oleagineux, 36, 169 - 228." type="journal article" year="1981">
Mariau 
<emphasis box="[1157,1207,841,866]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">et al</emphasis>
. 1981
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Herder, S. &amp; Fediere, G. &amp; Kouassi, K. N. &amp; Lery, X. &amp; Kouevidjin, R. &amp; Philippe, R. &amp; Mariau, D." pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="43 - 47" refId="ref35205" refString="Herder, S., Fediere, G., Kouassi, K. N., Lery, X., Kouevidjin, R., Philippe, R. &amp; Mariau, D. (1994) Mise en evidence de nouveaux virus a ARN chez Pteroteinon laufella Hewitson (Lepidoptera Hesperidae), defoliateur du palmier a huile en Cote-d'Ivoire. Discovery of new RNA viruses in Pteroteinon laufella Hewitson (Lepidoptera Hesperidae), an oil palm leaf eater in the Ivory Coast. Oleagineux, 49 (2), 43 - 47." type="journal article" year="1994">
Herder 
<emphasis box="[1379,1429,841,866]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">et al</emphasis>
. 1994
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D." box="[221,369,879,904]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refId="ref36315" refString="Mariau, D. (2000) Les ravageurs du palmier a huile et du cocotier: biologie, description et methodes de lutte. CIRAD, Montpellier, France, 1 disque optique numerique, CD-ROM." type="book" year="2000">Mariau 2000</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D." box="[381,438,879,904]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refId="ref36353" refString="Mariau, D. (2001) The fauna of oil palm and coconut: insect and mites pests and their natural enemies. CIRAD, Montpellier, 264 pp." type="book" year="2001">2001</bibRefCitation>
) lacks detail, but does include some photographs. The ova are laid in batches; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D. &amp; Desmier de Chenon, R. &amp; Julia, J. F. &amp; Philippe, R." pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="169 - 228" refId="ref36432" refString="Mariau, D., Desmier de Chenon, R., Julia, J. F. &amp; Philippe, R. (1981) Les ravageurs du palmier a huile et du cocotier en Afrique Occidentale. Oil palm and coconut pests in West Africa. Oleagineux, 36, 169 - 228." type="journal article" year="1981">
Mariau 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">et al</emphasis>
. (1981)
</bibRefCitation>
show a batch of 17 ova, which have a dark dorsal circle around the micropyle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1438,222,1755]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
The caterpillar is illustrated in black and white in 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D. &amp; Morin, J. P." box="[762,1035,957,982]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="187 - 188" refId="ref36384" refString="Mariau, D. &amp; Morin, J. P. (1974) Les ravageurs et maladies du palmier a huile et du cocotier. Chenilles defoliatrices de la famille des Hesperidae en Afrique Occidentale. Oleagineux, 29 (4), 187 - 188." type="journal article" year="1974">Mariau &amp; Morin (1974)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D. &amp; Desmier de Chenon, R. &amp; Julia, J. F. &amp; Philippe, R." box="[1047,1274,957,982]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="169 - 228" refId="ref36432" refString="Mariau, D., Desmier de Chenon, R., Julia, J. F. &amp; Philippe, R. (1981) Les ravageurs du palmier a huile et du cocotier en Afrique Occidentale. Oil palm and coconut pests in West Africa. Oleagineux, 36, 169 - 228." type="journal article" year="1981">
Mariau 
<emphasis box="[1136,1186,957,982]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">et al</emphasis>
. (1981)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Herder, S. &amp; Fediere, G. &amp; Kouassi, K. N. &amp; Lery, X. &amp; Kouevidjin, R. &amp; Philippe, R. &amp; Mariau, D." pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="43 - 47" refId="ref35205" refString="Herder, S., Fediere, G., Kouassi, K. N., Lery, X., Kouevidjin, R., Philippe, R. &amp; Mariau, D. (1994) Mise en evidence de nouveaux virus a ARN chez Pteroteinon laufella Hewitson (Lepidoptera Hesperidae), defoliateur du palmier a huile en Cote-d'Ivoire. Discovery of new RNA viruses in Pteroteinon laufella Hewitson (Lepidoptera Hesperidae), an oil palm leaf eater in the Ivory Coast. Oleagineux, 49 (2), 43 - 47." type="journal article" year="1994">
Herder 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">et al</emphasis>
. (1994)
</bibRefCitation>
, and in colour in 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D." box="[457,622,996,1021]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refId="ref36315" refString="Mariau, D. (2000) Les ravageurs du palmier a huile et du cocotier: biologie, description et methodes de lutte. CIRAD, Montpellier, France, 1 disque optique numerique, CD-ROM." type="book" year="2000">Mariau (2000)</bibRefCitation>
, which is reproduced here as 
<figureCitation box="[951,1083,996,1021]" captionStart="FIGURE 50" captionStartId="49.[151,250,1128,1150]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1106]" captionTargetId="figure-359@49.[151,1436,193,1106]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURE 50. Adult and caterpillar of Pteroteinon laufella. 1–2, adult, Port Harcourt, Nigeria [© D. Motshagen]; 3, final instar caterpillar (after Mariau et al. 1981, Mariau 2000) [© CIRAD]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920933" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920933/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Figure 50.3</figureCitation>
. The head is black with a broad brown stripe from vertex to clypeus, narrow at the vertex and widening evenly to include the adfrontals and part of the adjacent epicranium ventrally; conversely, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D. &amp; Morin, J. P." box="[697,979,1073,1098]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="187 - 188" refId="ref36384" refString="Mariau, D. &amp; Morin, J. P. (1974) Les ravageurs et maladies du palmier a huile et du cocotier. Chenilles defoliatrices de la famille des Hesperidae en Afrique Occidentale. Oleagineux, 29 (4), 187 - 188." type="journal article" year="1974">Mariau &amp; Morin (1974)</bibRefCitation>
describe the head of the caterpillar as golden brown (like 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Mariau &amp; Morin" authorityYear="1974" box="[369,500,1112,1135]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zophopetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerymica">
<emphasis box="[369,500,1112,1135]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Z. cerymica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) with broad brown patches on the sides (
<emphasis box="[956,1419,1111,1136]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">avec de larges taches brunes sur les côtés</emphasis>
). T1 white, black pronotum in the posterior half; spiracle conspicuous, orange-brown; legs black and white. Body greenish white; spiracles pale brown; legs brown; prolegs not visible. The pupa is dark in colour, with a distinctive bifurcate frontal projection (
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D. &amp; Morin, J. P." box="[481,749,1228,1253]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="187 - 188" refId="ref36384" refString="Mariau, D. &amp; Morin, J. P. (1974) Les ravageurs et maladies du palmier a huile et du cocotier. Chenilles defoliatrices de la famille des Hesperidae en Afrique Occidentale. Oleagineux, 29 (4), 187 - 188." type="journal article" year="1974">Mariau &amp; Morin 1974</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D. &amp; Desmier de Chenon, R. &amp; Julia, J. F. &amp; Philippe, R." box="[765,988,1228,1253]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="169 - 228" refId="ref36432" refString="Mariau, D., Desmier de Chenon, R., Julia, J. F. &amp; Philippe, R. (1981) Les ravageurs du palmier a huile et du cocotier en Afrique Occidentale. Oil palm and coconut pests in West Africa. Oleagineux, 36, 169 - 228." type="journal article" year="1981">
Mariau 
<emphasis box="[857,911,1228,1253]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">et al</emphasis>
. 1981
</bibRefCitation>
), similar to that of 
<taxonomicName box="[1224,1342,1229,1252]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pteroteinon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caenira">
<emphasis box="[1224,1342,1229,1252]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">P. caenira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 45" captionStartId="45.[151,250,1364,1386]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1340]" captionTargetId="figure-284@45.[151,1436,195,1340]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURE 45. Pupae of Pteroteinon caenira, collected 17 Mar 1993 on ornamental palm (?Dypsis lutescens), Ibadan, Nigeria. 1, dorsal view; 25mm; 94/101B; 2, lateral view 25mm; 94/101B; 3, lateral view formed up dead female pupa (mark in space 1B is a pin hole; frontal projection broken off); 94/101B; 4, lateral view formed up dead male pupa (head is missing); 94/101D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920922" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920922/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Figure 45.1–2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1438,222,1755]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,402,1305,1330]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Natural enemies.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D. &amp; Morin, J. P." box="[410,681,1305,1330]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="187 - 188" refId="ref36384" refString="Mariau, D. &amp; Morin, J. P. (1974) Les ravageurs et maladies du palmier a huile et du cocotier. Chenilles defoliatrices de la famille des Hesperidae en Afrique Occidentale. Oleagineux, 29 (4), 187 - 188." type="journal article" year="1974">Mariau &amp; Morin (1974)</bibRefCitation>
do not distinguish between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1868" box="[1001,1115,1305,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pteroteinon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laufella">
<emphasis box="[1001,1115,1305,1330]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">P. laufella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Mariau &amp; Morin" authorityYear="1974" box="[1171,1304,1306,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zophopetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerymica">
<emphasis box="[1171,1304,1306,1329]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Z. cerymica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, when they discuss the natural enemies of these two skippers. However, more recently, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D." box="[1044,1211,1343,1368]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refId="ref36353" refString="Mariau, D. (2001) The fauna of oil palm and coconut: insect and mites pests and their natural enemies. CIRAD, Montpellier, 264 pp." type="book" year="2001">Mariau (2001)</bibRefCitation>
treats all the same natural enemies under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1868" box="[404,516,1382,1407]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pteroteinon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laufella">
<emphasis box="[404,516,1382,1407]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">P. laufella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and mentions none for 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Mariau &amp; Morin" authorityYear="1974" box="[779,911,1383,1406]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zophopetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerymica">
<emphasis box="[779,911,1383,1406]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Z. cerymica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, so we follow this arrangement here. Although these two palm-feeding skippers may well have natural enemies in common, this should not be assumed. The ova are parasitized by a 
<taxonomicName box="[397,578,1460,1485]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Tetrastichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[397,533,1460,1485]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Tetrastichus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
and the pupae are host to tachinids, an ichneumonid and two chalcids: 
<taxonomicName box="[151,336,1498,1523]" class="Insecta" family="Chalcididae" genus="Brachymeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[151,297,1498,1523]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Brachymeria</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[390,542,1499,1522]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Stomatocerus</emphasis>
sp. As discussed in 
<bibRefCitation author="Cock, M. J. W." box="[768,924,1498,1523]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 63" refId="ref34130" refString="Cock, M. J. W. (2010 a) Observations on the biology of Afrotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera) principally from Kenya. Part 1. Introduction and Coeliadinae. Zootaxa, 2547, 1 - 63." type="journal article" year="2010">Cock (2010a)</bibRefCitation>
, the true host of the egg parasitoid 
<taxonomicName authority="Nixon" authorityName="Nixon" authorityYear="1935" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Telenomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoas">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Telenomus thoas</emphasis>
Nixon
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[303,440,1537,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Scelionidae</taxonomicName>
), described from ova of 
<taxonomicName box="[712,934,1537,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pyrrhochalcia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iphis">
<emphasis box="[712,934,1537,1562]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Pyrrhochalcia iphis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is probably 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1868" box="[1081,1304,1537,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pteroteinon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laufella">
<emphasis box="[1081,1304,1537,1562]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Pteroteinon laufella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1438,222,1755]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
Pathogens have also been recorded. In outbreaks, mortality due to two virulent RNA viruses can be high (
<bibRefCitation author="Herder, S. &amp; Fediere, G. &amp; Kouassi, K. N. &amp; Lery, X. &amp; Kouevidjin, R. &amp; Philippe, R. &amp; Mariau, D." box="[158,365,1614,1639]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="43 - 47" refId="ref35205" refString="Herder, S., Fediere, G., Kouassi, K. N., Lery, X., Kouevidjin, R., Philippe, R. &amp; Mariau, D. (1994) Mise en evidence de nouveaux virus a ARN chez Pteroteinon laufella Hewitson (Lepidoptera Hesperidae), defoliateur du palmier a huile en Cote-d'Ivoire. Discovery of new RNA viruses in Pteroteinon laufella Hewitson (Lepidoptera Hesperidae), an oil palm leaf eater in the Ivory Coast. Oleagineux, 49 (2), 43 - 47." type="journal article" year="1994">
Herder 
<emphasis box="[245,294,1614,1639]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">et al</emphasis>
. 1994
</bibRefCitation>
) and pupae may be killed by a 
<taxonomicName box="[715,869,1614,1639]" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Trichocomaceae" genus="Paecilomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Eurotiales" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[715,869,1614,1639]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Paecilomyces</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fungus (
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D. &amp; Desmier de Chenon, R. &amp; Julia, J. F. &amp; Philippe, R." box="[967,1180,1614,1639]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="169 - 228" refId="ref36432" refString="Mariau, D., Desmier de Chenon, R., Julia, J. F. &amp; Philippe, R. (1981) Les ravageurs du palmier a huile et du cocotier en Afrique Occidentale. Oil palm and coconut pests in West Africa. Oleagineux, 36, 169 - 228." type="journal article" year="1981">
Mariau 
<emphasis box="[1057,1105,1614,1639]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">et al</emphasis>
. 1981
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1438,222,1755]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,423,1653,1678]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Economic damage.</emphasis>
See under 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Mariau &amp; Morin" authorityYear="1974" box="[550,682,1654,1677]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zophopetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerymica">
<emphasis box="[550,682,1654,1677]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Z. cerymica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, regarding the comments in 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D. &amp; Morin, J. P." box="[1006,1278,1653,1678]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="187 - 188" refId="ref36384" refString="Mariau, D. &amp; Morin, J. P. (1974) Les ravageurs et maladies du palmier a huile et du cocotier. Chenilles defoliatrices de la famille des Hesperidae en Afrique Occidentale. Oleagineux, 29 (4), 187 - 188." type="journal article" year="1974">Mariau &amp; Morin (1974)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D. &amp; Desmier de Chenon, R. &amp; Julia, J. F. &amp; Philippe, R." pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="169 - 228" refId="ref36432" refString="Mariau, D., Desmier de Chenon, R., Julia, J. F. &amp; Philippe, R. (1981) Les ravageurs du palmier a huile et du cocotier en Afrique Occidentale. Oil palm and coconut pests in West Africa. Oleagineux, 36, 169 - 228." type="journal article" year="1981">
Mariau 
<emphasis box="[1379,1429,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">et al</emphasis>
. (1981)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D." box="[284,452,1692,1717]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refId="ref36315" refString="Mariau, D. (2000) Les ravageurs du palmier a huile et du cocotier: biologie, description et methodes de lutte. CIRAD, Montpellier, France, 1 disque optique numerique, CD-ROM." type="book" year="2000">Mariau (2000)</bibRefCitation>
, which treat 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1868" box="[602,716,1692,1717]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pteroteinon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laufella">
<emphasis box="[602,716,1692,1717]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">P. laufella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Mariau &amp; Morin" authorityYear="1974" box="[776,910,1693,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zophopetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerymica">
<emphasis box="[776,910,1693,1716]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Z. cerymica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
together. 
<bibRefCitation author="Herder, S. &amp; Fediere, G. &amp; Kouassi, K. N. &amp; Lery, X. &amp; Kouevidjin, R. &amp; Philippe, R. &amp; Mariau, D." box="[1026,1254,1692,1717]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="43 - 47" refId="ref35205" refString="Herder, S., Fediere, G., Kouassi, K. N., Lery, X., Kouevidjin, R., Philippe, R. &amp; Mariau, D. (1994) Mise en evidence de nouveaux virus a ARN chez Pteroteinon laufella Hewitson (Lepidoptera Hesperidae), defoliateur du palmier a huile en Cote-d'Ivoire. Discovery of new RNA viruses in Pteroteinon laufella Hewitson (Lepidoptera Hesperidae), an oil palm leaf eater in the Ivory Coast. Oleagineux, 49 (2), 43 - 47." type="journal article" year="1994">
Herder 
<emphasis box="[1112,1164,1692,1717]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">et al</emphasis>
. (1994)
</bibRefCitation>
refer to regular outbreaks of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1868" box="[297,410,1730,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pteroteinon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laufella">
<emphasis box="[297,410,1730,1755]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">P. laufella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on oil palm in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[684,838,1730,1755]" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Côte d’Ivoire</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
